100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 18, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on international disarmament and the ongoing challenges in post-World War I Europe. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes, charged with teaching evolution in Tennessee, captured national attention, highlighting the clash between modern science and traditional beliefs. Meanwhile, the political landscape in Germany grew tense as economic instability continued to provoke public unrest.
